The article discusses President Obama's Accountable Government Initiative, which aims to cut waste and make the government more open and responsive to the American public. The initiative focuses on six strategies: driving agency top priorities, cutting waste, reforming contracting, closing the IT gap, promoting accountability and innovation through open government, and attracting and motivating top talent. The article highlights the progress made in each strategy, such as reducing improper payments, improving hiring processes, and enhancing cybersecurity. The article emphasizes the importance of transparency, accountability, and collaboration in achieving meaningful performance improvement in government.